Here is an example of SCSS code for a web page layout with a header, sidebar, and main content area. The main content area will scroll independently from the rest of the page:

```
// Variables
$sidebar-width: 250px;

// Layout
body {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

header {
  height: 60px;
  background-color: #333;
  color: #fff;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}

main {
  display: flex;
  flex: 1;
  overflow-y: auto;
}

.sidebar {
  width: $sidebar-width;
  background-color: #eee;
  padding: 20px;
}

.content {
  flex: 1;
  padding: 20px;
}

// Media Queries
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .sidebar {
    display: none;
  }

  .content {
    width: 100%;
  }
}
```

In this example, we use flexbox for the layout. The header is fixed at the top with a height of 60px and a dark background color. The main content area is also a flex container with a flex-grow property of 1, which allows it to fill the remaining space. The sidebar has a fixed width of 250px and a light background color. The content area has padding to separate it from the sidebar.

The overflow-y property on the main content area allows it to scroll independently from the rest of the page. Finally, we add a media query to hide the sidebar on smaller screens and make the content area take up the full width of the page.
